				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p> The debate between the EU and the US on farm support highlights a number of significant points from an ACP perspective. The first is the inadequacy of current WTO rules on domestic support to agriculture if, despite an expansion of public financing of agricultural support programmes, WTO compliance is possible. The second point is the huge gap between the rhetoric and reality of OECD agricultural support programmes. While all the talk is of reducing public aid to OECD agricultural producers, the reality is that major OECD agricultural aid programmes are, in one form or another, expanding. This does not bode well for ACP producers hoping to gain from fundamental reform of OECD agricultural policies.</p>
		</div>
		
